                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/11–948: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Callanan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-09T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 9, 1948—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 9—5:41 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>133. Warning similar to Consulate General Shanghai sent to Americans today—this
                    district north of and bordering on Yangtze.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Callanan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
